---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Home Builder Portal"
  description="How Home Builder Portal collects, uses, and protects your information. Last updated March 2026."
>
  <section class="py-20 px-6 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h1 class="font-heading text-4xl font-bold text-primary mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-10">Last updated: March 1, 2026</p>

      <div class="space-y-10 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-primary mb-3">1. Who We Are</h2>
          <p>
            Home Builder Portal is a software-as-a-service platform for home builder companies.
            This privacy policy applies to our marketing website at
            <strong>www.homebuilderportal.com</strong> ("the Site"). For questions about this
            policy, contact us at <a
              href="mailto:hello@homebuilderportal.com"
              class="text-accent underline">hello@homebuilderportal.com</a
            >.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-primary mb-3">
            2. Information We Collect
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-3">We collect information in two ways:</p>
          <p class="mb-2">
            <strong class="text-gray-800">Information you provide directly.</strong> When you submit
            a demo request form on this Site, we collect your first name, last name, company name,
            work email address, phone number (if provided), and estimated homes built per year. This
            information is used solely to schedule and conduct your product demo.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong class="text-gray-800">Information collected automatically.</strong> When you visit
            the Site, we may collect standard analytics data including pages visited, time on site,
            browser type, device type, and general geographic region. This data is collected in
            aggregate and is not linked to your personal identity.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-primary mb-3">
            3. How We Use Your Information
          </h2>
          <ul class="flex flex-col gap-2 pl-4">
            {
              [
                'To contact you and schedule your requested product demo',
                'To send a confirmation email when you submit a demo request',
                'To understand how visitors use our Site and improve the experience',
                'To comply with legal obligations',
              ].map((item) => (
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                  <span class="text-accent font-bold flex-shrink-0 mt-1" aria-hidden="true">
                    –
                  </span>
                  {item}
                </li>
              ))
            }
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-4">
            We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal information to third parties.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-primary mb-3">4. Cookies & Analytics</h2>
          <p class="mb-3">
            This Site uses Google Analytics 4 (GA4) to collect anonymized usage data. GA4 uses
            cookies — small text files stored in your browser — to help us understand how visitors
            use the Site. The data collected includes pages visited, session duration, and general
            device/browser information. GA4 data is processed by Google in accordance with their
            privacy policy.
          </p>
          <p>
            You can opt out of Google Analytics tracking by installing the
            <a
              href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="text-accent underline">Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on</a
            >, or by adjusting your browser's cookie settings. Our Site will function normally
            without analytics cookies.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-primary mb-3">
            5. Third-Party Services
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-3">
            We use the following third-party services to operate this Site:
          </p>
          <ul class="flex flex-col gap-2 pl-4">
            {
              [
                'Web3Forms — processes demo request form submissions and sends confirmation emails. Your form data is transmitted to Web3Forms servers to deliver these communications.',
                'Google Analytics — collects anonymized usage data as described above.',
                'Google Fonts — loads typefaces from Google servers. Google may collect basic request data (IP address, browser type) when fonts are loaded.',
                'Cloudflare Pages — hosts and serves this website.',
              ].map((item) => (
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                  <span class="text-accent font-bold flex-shrink-0 mt-1" aria-hidden="true">
                    –
                  </span>
                  {item}
                </li>
              ))
            }
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-primary mb-3">6. Data Retention</h2>
          <p>
            Form submission data (your name, email, company, and phone number) is retained for as
            long as necessary to conduct your demo and any subsequent sales conversations. If you
            are not interested in proceeding after your demo, you may request deletion of your
            information at any time by emailing us at
            <a href="mailto:hello@homebuilderportal.com" class="text-accent underline"
              >hello@homebuilderportal.com</a
            >.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-primary mb-3">7. Your Rights</h2>
          <p class="mb-3">
            Depending on your location, you may have rights regarding your personal data,
            including the right to access, correct, delete, or restrict processing of your
            information. To exercise any of these rights, contact us at
            <a href="mailto:hello@homebuilderportal.com" class="text-accent underline"
              >hello@homebuilderportal.com</a
            >.
          </p>
          <p>
            We will respond to all requests within 30 days.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-primary mb-3">8. Data Security</h2>
          <p>
            This Site is served over HTTPS. Form submissions are transmitted securely to our
            form processing provider. While we take reasonable precautions to protect your
            information, no internet transmission is completely secure.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-primary mb-3">9. Children's Privacy</h2>
          <p>
            This Site is intended for business professionals and is not directed at children under
            the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-primary mb-3">
            10. Changes to This Policy
          </h2>
          <p>
            We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will update the
            "Last updated" date at the top of this page. Continued use of the Site after any
            changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-primary mb-3">11. Contact</h2>
          <p>
            Questions about this Privacy Policy? Email us at
            <a href="mailto:hello@homebuilderportal.com" class="text-accent underline"
              >hello@homebuilderportal.com</a
            >.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
